2023-05-08T14:05:19: Velocity area station on the Blackadder Water.
Velocity area station. Natural river section, about 13m wide, with rock control.
Moderate seasonal weed growth effects rating. Peak flow ratings derived from current meter gaugings up to 2.4m (about 2 QMED), simple extrapolation beyond.
Full period of record peak flow data reviewed and released in September 2022 (WINFAP Files v11).
Natural catchment. Mostly Old Red Sandstone and calciferous sandstone overlain by Boulder Clay. Grazing on hills, arable on lower land; some forest. No significant catchment changes known.
